article.description: Vermont beats UMBC 71-54, rises to 4-0 in conference
article.headline: Vermont beats UMBC 71-54, rises to 4-0 in conference
article.linkText: Vermont beats UMBC 71-54, rises to 4-0 in conference
article.story: BALTIMORE -- Ethan O'Day scored 15 points on 7 of 9 shooting and Brendan Kilpatrick added 13 points as nine players scored in Vermont's 71-54 victory over UMBC on Saturday. O'Day opened the game with a layup and a shot block as Vermont cruised to a 16-4 lead. Trae Bell-Haynes added 10 points and six assists for the Catamounts (9-8, 4-0 America East). Wayne Sparrow, who led the Retrievers (2-15, 0-4) with 20 points, poured in two layups and a jump shot to spark a 10-2 run that closed the gap to 18-16 and forced a Vermont timeout. Cody Joyce scored 14 and Jourdan Grant 12. UMBC stayed close, and the first half ended 33-31, Vermont. The Catamounts opened the second half on an 11-2 run with three O'Day layups and a Kurt Steidl 3-pointer to break away. Vermont made 25 of 46 field goals (54 percent) with 17 assists.
